5 Okay 20 of use went to Sin city for sushi. We made reservations for lunch, they hesitated for a moment because of the size of the group. In the end they did accommodate us and they gave the royal treatment. They had brought in extra sushi chefs to meet the demand for that day. This place is not that big 10 people on the sushi bar. 4 booths and a table that holds about 16 people in the center. Now the food.   The fish was pretty fresh, no fishiness that I find at some all you can eat sushi. I can tell when I order salmon and yellow-tail if anyone of those is fishy then its not fresh. My only complaint was the nigiri sushi had too much rice to fish ratio.   The rolls were good, my fav double seared, wet dream and stacie. Finish off with a no name hand roll.   We all liked this place because of the servers and the sushi chefs especially Jesse were so upbeat and friendly to us. Everyone definitely liked this place more than Island sushi (sorry that used to be our fav). Also there was no time limit so no rush.   For an all you can eat sushi in vegas this is as good as it gets in my opinion. I'll be bringing back the group again soon. Hopefully this time I'll get to see Jimbo former owner of Manda sushi and the original all you can eat sushi bar in Las Vegas. Too bad they had to close due to a smoking law, it was inside a bar.
